{
    "name": "Raven",
    "type": "creature",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Raven",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "These omnivorous birds are cunning and opportunistic scavengers. Capable of solving simple puzzles in order to retrieve desired items, ravens gather at the periphery of civilization, raiding it as needed when they are not hunting in the wilds. Whether singularly, in pairs, or as a flock, ravens live off scraps as often as they do carrion or prey. They are also unusually social among their own kind, even alerting other ravens to large carcasses with loud, croaking cries; it is rumored that this extends between flocks as well.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Animal</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"10\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Nature</a></u>)</b>: DC 13",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Bestiary 2",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Bestiary 2 pg. 221",
                        "alt": "Bestiary 2 pg. 221",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq022yq"
                    },
                    "page": 221
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Raven",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Raven Traders",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Given enough time to develop the relationship and establish what you want, it is possible to engage a raven in a sort of trade. Placing a small, shiny object where the raven can take it might entice it to grab the prize and fly off, returning 3d6 minutes later with something from its own stash. Convincing a raven to trade requires a DC 20 <a aonid=\"10\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Nature</a> check to <a aonid=\"58\" game-obj=\"Actions\">Command an Animal</a> and, of course, a raven who has the inclination to trade with you in the first place.",
                    "sources": {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Bestiary 2",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Bestiary 2 pg. 221",
                            "alt": "Bestiary 2 pg. 221",
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq022yq"
                        },
                        "page": 221
                    },
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "treasure_and_rewards",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Treasure and Rewards",
                    "image": "Sidebar_5_TreasureAndRewards.png"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Few birds are as cunning and social as the raven.",
            "sources": {
                "type": "source",
                "name": "Bestiary 2",
                "link": {
                    "type": "link",
                    "name": "Bestiary 2 pg. 221",
